		<h1>Settings</h1>
		<hr>

		<h4>Every Mixture project should contain a simple <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JSON">JSON</a> file in the root called <code>mixture.json</code>.</h4>
		<pre class="prettyprint linenums pad"><ol class="linenums"><li class="L0"><span class="pun">{</span></li><li class="L1"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"debug"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">false</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L2"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"lintScripts"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">false</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L3"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"preprocessorLocations"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">null</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L4"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"preprocessorScriptOutput"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">null</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L5"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"preprocessorStyleOutput"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">null</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L6"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"projectName"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="str">"Your project name"</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L7"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"projectDescription"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="str">"Your project description"</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L8"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"publishedId"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">null</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L9"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"serverHostname"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">null</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L0"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"serverPort"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">null</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L1"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"templateDirectory"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="str">"templates"</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L2"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"templateDefaultLayout"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="str">"layout"</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L3"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"templateDefaultPage"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="str">"index"</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L4"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"type"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="str">"mixture"</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L5"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"useCompass"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">false</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L6"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"simpleModePartnerServer"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">null</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L7"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"modelSource"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">null</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L8"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"domain"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">null</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L9"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"followLeader"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">true</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L0"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"customRuby"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">false</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L1"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"customRubyPath"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">null</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L2"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"routes"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">null</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L3"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"remoteDebugPort"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="lit">0</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L4"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"simpleModeFileTypes"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">null</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L5"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"optimiseImages"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">true</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L6"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"password"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">null</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L7"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"ignoreDir"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="str">"ignore"</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L8"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"customTodos"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln">  </span><span class="kwd">null</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L9"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"autoPrefixer"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">null</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L0"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"sass"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">null</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L1"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"sitemap"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">false</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L2"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"convertHtml"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">null</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L3"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"less"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">null</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L4"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"optimiseSVG"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="kwd">true</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L5"><span class="pln">  </span><span class="str">"reload"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="lit">0</span></li><li class="L6"><span class="pun">}</span></li></ol></pre>

		<p>Below is a breakdown of each element:</p>
		<ul>
			<li><code>debug</code> true or false, <a href="/optimise#debug">more information</a>.</li>
			<li><code>lintScripts</code> true or false, tells Mixture to lint scripts when updated, <a href="/optimise#lint">more information</a>.</li>
			<li><code>preprocessorLocations</code> sets the (folder) locations within your project that Mixture will handle preprocessing, minifcation &amp; linting. eg <code>"preprocessorLocations": ["public/styles", "public/scripts"]</code>. if <code>null</code> no processing will happen.</li>
			<li><code>preprocessorScriptOutput</code> sets the output directory of any preprocessed scripts. If <code>null</code> they will be compiled in the same location as the source file.</li>
			<li><code>preprocessorStyleOutput</code> sets the output directory of any preprocessed styles. If <code>null</code> they will be compiled in the same location as the source file.</li>
			<li><code>projectName</code> name of the project.</li>
			<li><code>projectDescription</code> description of the project.</li>
			<li><code>publishedId</code> once published to the Mixture servers this will be populated with a unique project id.</li>
			<li><code>serverHostname</code> when set to <code>null</code> Mixture will attempt use your internal network address, if this fails it will fallback to "localhost" to use a custom hostname, please view <a href="http://support.mixture.io/kb/custom-host-name">our support site</a>.</li>
			<li><code>serverPort</code> tells Mixture what port to use when running locally, if <code>null</code> Mixture will use an available port.</li>
			<li><code>templateDirectory</code> if you are building a Mixture project then all of your template files should be located within this folder, this folder requires two sub-directories: "layouts" and "includes" (these sub-directories can not be renamed).</li>
			<li><code>templateDefaultLayout</code> sets the default layout file for pages. This should be set to the name of your default layout within your "templates/layouts" folder without the <code>.liquid</code> extension. eg <code>"templateDefaultLayout": "layout"</code>. You can stop all templates using a layout by setting to: "none", "" or null.</li>
			<li><code>templateDefaultPage</code> this tells mixture which template file to use as the root document (homepage). This should be set to the name of the page without the <code>.liquid</code> extension. eg <code>"templateDefaultPage": "index"</code></li>
			<li><code>type</code> this tells Mixture what type of project it is and how to handle (currently only "mixture" and "simple" available).</li>
			<li><code>useCompass</code> if true tells Mixture not to handle Sass preprocessing and instead hands over to Compass. Mixture will still report issues.</li>
			<li><code>simpleModePartnerServer</code> if you are using Mixture in "simple" mode with another server (rails, mamp, etc) but still want to benefit from Mixture's multi-device and live refresh features, simple enter the address of the other server. eg <code>"simpleModePartnerServer": "http://localhost:1234"</code></li>
			<li><code>modelSource</code> allows you to swap the local model system for online models.</li>
			<li><code>domain</code> <a href="/mixture#hosting">add a custom domain</a> to your online published project.</li>
			<li><code>followLeader</code> expects true or false, default is true. Enables &amp; disables "follow the leader" functionality when using with multiple devices / browsers.</li>
			<li><code>customRuby</code> tells Mixture to use a custom version of Ruby, <a href="/custom-ruby">read more about custom Ruby</a>.</li>
			<li><code>customRubyPath</code> allows you to override the path(s) to your own install of Ruby, <a href="/custom-ruby">read more about custom Ruby</a>.</li>
			<li><code>routes</code> allows custom routes and redirects for your project <a href="/routes">read more.</a></li>
			<li><code>remoteDebugPort</code> set this port to enable remote debugging for devices, Mixture uses weinre – <a href="http://people.apache.org/~pmuellr/weinre/docs/latest/">read more.</a> When you open a project with this port set, mixture will alert you with the address you can use to start debugging with.</li>
			<li><code>simpleModeFileTypes</code> sets the file types that will cause a reload / refresh in simple mode. eg <code>"simpleModeFileTypes": [".php", ".css"]</code> — if this is not set (null) Mixture will reload all files.</li>
			<!--<li><code>useNodeSass</code> expects true or false, this feature essentially lets node-sass (libsass) take over processing Sass (compass will still use the standard ruby processing). <code>Important!</code> libsass which node-sass depends on is behind the current Ruby Sass release and so not all features are supported, also only the Scss syntax is suported. The benefit is speed - it's very fast almost instant. On Windows when set to true for the first time you may be prompted to confirm Mixture can install node-sass.</li>-->
			<li><code>optimiseImages</code> expects true or false, when set to true Mixture will optimise images when added to the project using optipng and jpegtran.</li>
			<li><code>password</code> allows you to secure a published project with a password. To remove set back to null.</li>
			<li><code>ignoreDir</code> allows you to set an array of project directories that will be ignored by publish, convert to html and any preprocessing logic eg <code>"ignoreDir": ["assets","public/css"]</code>.</li>
			<li><code>customTodos</code> please see the <a href="/mixture#to-dos">To-do section</a>.</li>
			<li><code>autoPrefixer</code> please see the <a href="/autoprefix">Autoprefix section</a>.</li>
			<li><code>sass</code> please see the <a href="/preprocessors#sass">Sass section</a>.</li>
			<li><code>sitemap</code> please see the <a href="/sitemap">Sitemap section</a>.</li>
			<!--<li><code>convertHtmlExtension</code> allows you to define the extension used when converting to HTML (can also be null or "" if you don't require extension) - default is <code>.html</code>.</li>
			<li><code>convertHtmlOutput</code> allows you to define a custom location for the output of "convert to HTML" eg <code>"convertHtmlOutput": "/users/xxxx/desktop/example"</code> (format with forward slahes as shown in the example).</li>
			<li><code>convertHtmlIgnore</code> comma seperated list of URLs that should be ignored when converting to HTML eg <code>"convertHtmlIgnore": "/articles,/about"</code>.</li>
			<li><code>convertHtmlDefault</code> used if you wish for folders and default files to be created on convert to HTML eg <code>"convertHtmlDefault": "index"</code> in this case "about.liquid" would be converted to "/about/index.html" - the default document extension used is automatically handled by "convertHtmlExtension" or ".html" by default.</li>-->
			<li><code>convertHtml</code> please see the <a href="/convert-html">convert Html section</a>.</li>
			<li><code>less</code> please see the <a href="/preprocessors#less">Less section</a>.</li>
			<li><code>optimiseSVG</code> when true will optimise any SVGs added to the project while Mixture is running.</li>
 	    	<li><code>reload</code> Delays or disables live reload and style injection. 0 = no delay. -1 = disabled. Anything above 0 and below 10000, will delay in milliseconds.</li>
         </ul>
	</section>

	<!-- Section: Live -->
	<section id="live">

		<h1>Live Refresh &amp; Multi-device testing</h1>
		<hr>

		<h4>Mixture will automatically reload or style inject when it detects changes in your project. This feature will work on most browsers and devices and is perfect for multi-device testing.</h4>
		<p>The Mixture live refresh feature also implements "follow the leader", this means any device / browser connected will change to reflect the one being navigated.</p>
		<p>Mixture will automatically manage live reload on your behalf, you don't need to add any tags set anything up - just get busy building!</p>
		<p>Mixture will also list all connected devices and if you set a "remoteDebugPort" in the Mixture settings, you can even click a device from Mixture to automatically open a <a href="http://people.apache.org/~pmuellr/weinre/docs/latest/Home.html">WEINRE</a> debug page for that device.</p>
		<p class="callout callout-info">Changes to styles (stylesheets) are <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ER-la4wunyo&amp;hd=1">injected instead of a browser refresh</a>.</p>

	</section>

	<!-- Section: Local -->
	<section id="local">

		<h1>Local Server</h1>
		<hr>

		<h4>Mixture has a built-in local server for running Mixture projects.</h4>
		<p>When opening / starting a Mixture project, the server will be started on port <code>7774</code> if this is not possible an available port will be selected. Mixture will attempt to connect to your local network (this allows you easily to connect and test across devices on your local network), if you are not on a network or Mixture can not connect it will default to <code>localhost</code>.</p>
		<p class="callout callout-info">You can override this behaviour and set your preffered hostname and port via the Mixture settings. If you are using the Windows version you may be prompted to confirm Mixture access to the port and hostsname.<br><br>If Mixture is unable to use the port set, it will always fallback to 7774 or any available port.</p>
		<p class="callout callout-info">If you encounter issues starting the server from "view locally" or it is greyed out, please visit our <a href="http://support.mixture.io/">support site and knowldege base</a>.</p>

	</section>

	<!-- Section: Boilerplates -->
	<section id="boilerplates">

		<h1>Boilerplates</h1>
		<hr>

		<h4>Boilerplates allow you to jump start a project quickly &amp; easily. Some of the more popular boilerplates are already available in Mixture, but you can also create and share your own.</h4>
		<p class="callout callout-info">Please make sure your boilerplate fully works before you make public, we will test and remove if we find issues. It's also worth making sure that you do not have any custom settings that may not be replicated outside of your machine (custom ruby for example).</p>
		<p class="callout callout-info">Unless explicitly detailed as to why it doesn't, please ensure that your boilerplate works when published to the Mixture servers - failing to do either of these may result in your boilerplate being switched to private.</p>
		<p>The following is a brief explanation as to how you can add your own private or public boilerplates to Mixture.</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Boilerplates are simply Mixture projects, the best way to get started is to create a new empty project folder, open with Mixture and select the "Empty" boilerplate.</li>
			<li>Once downloaded and running, edit the project, settings and build your perfect starting point.</li>
			<li>To add your boilerplate to Mixture you will first need to add your project as a Git repository and push it to GitHub (<a href="https://help.github.com/">view more details about getting started with Git and GitHub</a>).</li>
			<li>Once your project is successfully in GitHub and you have a URL for this new repository, <a href="https://accounts.mixture.io/boilerplates">login to your online Mixture account</a>.</li>
			<li>Once signed in and if not already in the Boilerplates section, select Boilerplates from the main navigation.</li>
			<li>You can now fill in some basic details and add your boilerplate as outlined, you can also manage your boilerplates from this area.</li>
		</ul>

	</section>

	<!-- Section: To-Dos -->
	<section id="to-dos">

		<h1>Smart To-dos</h1>
		<hr>

		<h4>A helpful feature of Mixture is the ability to add to-dos in your code, to-dos are essentially comments, but they come in 3 flavours depending on what type of file or element you are adding them to...</h4>
		<pre class="prettyprint linenums pad"><ol class="linenums"><li class="L0"><span class="com">&lt;!-- TODO: I must not forget to close all of my html tags! --&gt;</span></li></ol></pre>

		<p>Can be used in the following file types: <code>Liquid</code>.</p>
		<pre class="prettyprint linenums pad"><ol class="linenums"><li class="L0"><span class="com">/* TODO: I must not forget to finish this project! */</span></li></ol></pre>

		<p>Can be used in the following file types: <code>CSS</code>, <code>Sass</code>, <code>Scss</code>, <code>Less</code>, <code>JavaScript</code> or <code>Liquid</code> (when used in an inline style or script block).</p>

		<p class="callout callout-info">These style comments used in preprocessors like Sass won't be picked up in the source file, but will be picked up in the output.</p>
		<pre class="prettyprint linenums pad"><ol class="linenums"><li class="L0"><span class="com"># TODO: I must not forget how many coffees I've drunk today! #</span></li></ol></pre>

		<p>Can be used in the following file types: <code>CoffeeScript</code>.</p>
		<pre class="prettyprint linenums pad"><ol class="linenums"><li class="L0"><span class="pun">-</span><span class="com"># TODO: I must check my indents, tabs or spaces?</span></li></ol></pre>

		<p>Can be used in the following file types: <code>Haml</code>.</p>
		<pre class="prettyprint linenums pad"><ol class="linenums"><li class="L0"><span class="com">// TODO: preprocessing is so cool!</span></li></ol></pre>

		<p>Can be used in the following file types: <code>Sass</code>, <code>Scss</code>, <code>Less</code> &amp; <code>Styl</code>.</p>
		<p>When Mixture detects a to-do it will automatically add and display the to-do within the application for easy access, clicking on a to-do within Mixture will open the file with the to-do within your default editor (for that file type).</p>

		<h3>Custom To-dos</h3>
		<p>You can create custom to-do logic and also define the file types that are affected</p>
		<p>To do this you need to make an addition to the settings file, the following example shows you how to add support for to-do's in PHP, CS and Jade files.</p><p>
		</p><pre class="prettyprint linenums pad"><ol class="linenums"><li class="L0"><span class="str">"customTodos"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="pun">[</span></li><li class="L1"><span class="pln">	</span><span class="pun">{</span></li><li class="L2"><span class="pln">		</span><span class="str">"fileTypes"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="str">"php,cs"</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L3"><span class="pln">		</span><span class="str">"regex"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="str">"(?&lt;=/[*] TODO:).*?(?=[*]/)"</span></li><li class="L4"><span class="pln">	</span><span class="pun">},</span></li><li class="L5"><span class="pln">	</span><span class="pun">{</span></li><li class="L6"><span class="pln">		</span><span class="str">"fileTypes"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="str">"jade"</span><span class="pun">,</span></li><li class="L7"><span class="pln">		</span><span class="str">"regex"</span><span class="pun">:</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="str">"(?&lt;=//- TODO:).*?(?=$)"</span></li><li class="L8"><span class="pln">	</span><span class="pun">}</span></li><li class="L9"><span class="pun">]</span></li></ol></pre>

	</section>

